Reproducing figure 4

Load the calculated AUC for each interaction of each computational methods.

library(ggplot2)
df_intr_auc = readRDS("ALL_region_auc_df.RDS")

Plot a boxplot of the AUC values for each computational method. Since we used 5-fold cross-validation, we have 5 AUC values for each interaction.

plot_list = list()
intr.list = unique(df_intr_auc$intr)

for (intr in intr.list){
  intr.df = df_intr_auc[df_intr_auc$intr == intr, ]
  p <- ggplot(intr.df, aes(x = feature, y = AUC, fill = feature)) +
    geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0.7) +  # Suppress outliers for clarity
    geom_jitter(width = 0.2, alpha = 0.5, size = 1) +  # Add jittered points
    cowplot::theme_cowplot() +
    labs(
      title = intr,
      x = "Feature",
      y = "AUC"
    ) +
    theme(
      plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 8, face = "bold"),
      axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 25, hjust = 1),
      legend.position = "right"
    ) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c(
        "CytoSignal" = "#1F77B4",
        "LIANA+" = "#FF7F0E", 
        "NICHES" = "#2CA02C",
        "SpatialDM" = "#D62728",
        "stLearn" = "#9467BD"
    ))

  # Append the plot to the list
  plot_list[[intr]] <- p
}

ggarrange(plotlist = plot_list, ncol = 3, nrow = 2, common.legend = TRUE, legend = "right")

Load the data and plot the calculated AUC for each interaction of each computational methods.

df_intr_auc = readRDS("ALL_cluster_auc_df.RDS")

df_plot <- df_intr_auc %>%
  dplyr::group_by(cluster, feature, intr) %>%
  dplyr::summarize(mean_AUC = mean(AUC, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop")

plot_list = list()
intr.list = unique(df_intr_auc$intr)

for (intr in intr.list){
  intr.df = df_plot[df_plot$intr == intr, ]
  intr.df = intr.df[intr.df$mean_AUC != 0, ]

  # Calculate cluster order based on max value
  cluster_order <- intr.df %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    summarise(max_value = max(mean_AUC)) %>%
    arrange(-max_value) %>%
    pull(cluster)
  
  intr.df$cluster = factor(intr.df$cluster, levels = cluster_order)

  n_clusters <- length(cluster_order)
  # browser()
  if (n_clusters == 1) {
    warning("Less than 2 clusters found for signal:", signal, "-", corr_type)
    separator_pos <- c(1.5)
  } else if (n_clusters == 0) {
    warning("No clusters found for signal:", signal, "-", corr_type)
    return()
  } else {
    separator_pos <- seq(1.5, n_clusters - 0.5, by = 1)
  }

  p <- ggplot(intr.df, aes(x = cluster, y = mean_AUC)) +
  geom_point(
    aes(alpha = feature, color = feature),  # Alpha mapped to cluster
    position = position_jitter(width = 0.2),
    size = 3
  ) +
  geom_vline(
    xintercept = separator_pos,
    linetype = "dotted",
    color = "gray50",
    alpha = 0.4,
    linewidth = 0.5
  ) +
  scale_alpha_manual(  # Cluster-specific transparency
    name = "Cluster transparency",
    values = c(
      "CytoSignal" = 1,
      "stLearn" = 0.3, 
      "SpatialDM" = 0.3,
      "LIANA+" = 0.3,
      "NICHES" = 0.3
    ) # Replace with your cluster names/values
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(
      "CytoSignal" = "#1F77B4",
      "LIANA+" = "#FF7F0E", 
      "NICHES" = "#2CA02C",
      "SpatialDM" = "#D62728",
      "stLearn" = "#9467BD"
    ))+
  labs(
    title = intr,
    y = "mean AUC",
    x = "Cluster (ordered by max value)"
  ) +
  cowplot::theme_cowplot() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.box = "vertical"  # Handle multiple legends
  )

  plot_list[[intr]] <- p

}

ggarrange(plotlist = plot_list, ncol = 1, common.legend = TRUE, legend = "right")
